data.name: Utils_FinalCheckIn.ToolTip
data.value:
After Final Check-In, materials are deleted from the database except for any historical records. Reference Numbers will not repeat unless removed from history.
Deselect this box to make the item available for check-out again.

data.name: AddMaterials_ProgramStockTypeRadio.ToolTip
data.value: Program Stock materials are visible to all users. Upon use of these materials, users must specify how many units were used and for what Shop Order. One reference number will be created. Add another if multiple unit sizes are available. Specify the total quantity of material available to be used, and the quantity to be decremented for each use. Ex: 10 rolls of tape in stock = 10 total qty; Each roll of tape is cut into 40 strips = 0.025 per use.

data.name: AddMaterials_UserStockTypeRadio.ToolTip
data.value: User Stock materials can be checked out by a user for their own use. One Reference Number is created for each unit of material which can be checked out. Specify the number of units available for check-out.

data.name: AddMaterials_CompactLabelCheck.ToolTip
data.value:
Prints a label with two columns of data instead of one. This label can be trimmed to less than 0.5in height, but is typically twice the width of regular labels.
